Difference between walk, trail, Path, Circuit, Cycle
i) Open walk => Start at specific point, end at other point except started one.
ii) Closed walk => Start at specific point, end at same point
i) Open trail => Start at specific point, end at other point except started one.
ii) Closed trail OR Circuit => Start at specific point, end at same point
i) Open path => Start at specific point, end at other point except started one.
ii) Closed path OR Cycle => Start at specific point, end at same point
Euler Path OR Open Trail or Semi Euler Graph :- Edge can't be repeated i.e (a e d).
Euler Circuit OR Euler Cycle OR Closed Trail OR Euler Graph :- Every edge must be visited once i.e (a e d b e c).
Connected Graph :- Path between two vertices.
Hamiltonian Cycle OR Hamiltonian Cycle OR Hamiltonian Circuit OR Closed Path :- Every vertex must be visited once i.e (a e d b e c).
Hamiltonian Path OR Open Path :- Vertex can't be repeated i.e (a e d).
